1. There was a group receiving 4,000 IU/day of vitamin D3.
2. There was a group receiving 2,000 IU/day of vitamin D3.
3. The increase in quality life scores (SIBDQ) was significant in the group receiving 4,000 IU/day of vitamin D3.
4. The increase in quality life scores (SIBDQ) was not significant in the group receiving 2,000 IU/day of vitamin D3.
5. The increase in quality life scores (SIBDQ) for the 4,000 IU/day group was 1.0 ± 1.0.
6. The increase in quality life scores (SIBDQ) for the 2,000 IU/day group was 0.1 ± 1.0.
7. The p-value for the 4,000 IU/day group was 0.017.
8. The p-value for the 2,000 IU/day group was 0.87.
